casebody.data:
Steven T. HUMPHREY, Appellant/Petitioner(s),
v.
STATE of Florida, Appellee/Respondent(s). CASE NO.: 2D18-1155 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Second District. May 18, 2018

BY ORDER OF THE COURT:

This appeal is dismissed for lack of jurisdiction because the notice of appeal was filed more than 30 days after rendition of the orders asserted by appellant as being appealed and is, therefore, untimely. Appellant's motion for clarification of sentence is dismissed as moot.

BLACK, SALARIO, and ROTHSTEIN-YOUAKIM, JJ, Concur.
